{meta: title Will You Walk With Me}
{meta: artist Mary Duff}
{meta: writer Isla Grant}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Will you walk with me
Through the [F]darkest [C]night when my world goes wrong
Will you [F]make it [C]right will you [G7]guide my lips
In [C]all I say will you walk with [G7]me every [C]day
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
When I'm tired and weak
Will you [F]make me [C]strong when my mind's confused
And all [F]hope is [C]gone will you [G7]take my hand
You [C]lead the way dear Lord will you [G7]walk with me [C]today
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Will you [F]walk with me and ease my pain
Will you [C]walk with me give me hope once again
When my [F]eyes grow dim will you let me see 
Dear [C]Lord will you [G7]walk with [C]me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
If my friends should go
